items.title: Awesome Ocaml
items.content_text:
### Large Source Code Examples

*   [Base (⭐930)](https://github.com/janestreet/base) - Standard library for OCaml
*   [pfff (⭐184)](https://github.com/returntocorp/pfff) - an OCaml API to write static analysis, dynamic analysis, code visualizations, code navigations, or style-preserving source-to-source transformations such as refactorings on source code.
*   [cil (⭐376)](https://github.com/cil-project/cil) - C Intermediate Language
*   [coq (⭐5.1k)](https://github.com/coq/coq) - formal proof management system
*   [frama-c](https://git.frama-c.com/pub/frama-c) - platform dedicated to the analysis of source code written in C
*   [libguestfs (⭐666)](https://github.com/libguestfs/libguestfs) - library and tools for accessing and modifying virtual machine disk images
*   [Liquidsoap (⭐1.5k)](https://github.com/savonet/liquidsoap) - a swiss-army knife for multimedia streaming, notably used for netradios and webtvs
*   [mirage (⭐2.7k)](https://github.com/mirage/mirage) -  library operating system that constructs unikernels for secure, high-performance network applications across a variety of cloud computing and mobile platforms
*   [MLDonkey (⭐294)](https://github.com/ygrek/mldonkey) - cross-platform multi-network peer-to-peer daemon
*   [WHY3](https://gitlab.inria.fr/why3/why3) - platform for deductive program verification
items.content_html:
Large Source Code Examples

  • Base (⭐930) - Standard library for OCaml
  • pfff (⭐184) - an OCaml API to write static analysis, dynamic analysis, code visualizations, code navigations, or style-preserving source-to-source transformations such as refactorings on source code.
  • cil (⭐376) - C Intermediate Language
  • coq (⭐5.1k) - formal proof management system
  • frama-c - platform dedicated to the analysis of source code written in C
  • libguestfs (⭐666) - library and tools for accessing and modifying virtual machine disk images
  • Liquidsoap (⭐1.5k) - a swiss-army knife for multimedia streaming, notably used for netradios and webtvs
  • mirage (⭐2.7k) - library operating system that constructs unikernels for secure, high-performance network applications across a variety of cloud computing and mobile platforms
  • MLDonkey (⭐294) - cross-platform multi-network peer-to-peer daemon
  • WHY3 - platform for deductive program verification
